Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}
into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Green Bell Pepper{1} into
strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Toss bell pepper on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt,
and pepper. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-22%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast potatoes on top rack and bell
> peppers on middle rack.

Remove from sheet.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened,
~{5-7%minutes}. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and remaining Fry Seasoning; season
with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

While onion and beef cook, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}
and half the @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step).
Season with salt and pepper.

Slice @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.
Toast cut sides up in oven until lightly golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once beef is cooked through, stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, remaining
mustard, and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Top beef mixture with
@pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}; cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fill baguettes with beef filling and roasted bell pepper. Place cut sides up on
sheet used for veggies; sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake until
cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide sandwiches and potato wedges between plates. Top sandwiches with
@?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with creamy mustard on the side for
dipping.